The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Malik doubtful
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Malik doubtful
                      
	Karachi: Handicapped by the absence of their pace spearhead Umar Gul, Pakistan need to sort out their bowling combination when they take on a confident Sri Lanka in the super four stage of Asia Cup here on Sunday. To add to their woes, captain Shoaib Malik is also doubtful for Sundays match, coach Geoff Lawson said         
	Malik, who suffered cramps during his innings against India the other day, did not participate in Saturdays net session and worked with the physiotherapist on light exercises.           (PTI)                                                                                                                      
